com.viaoa.jsp

Class OAToggleButton

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.viaoa.jsp.OAButton
      • com.viaoa.jsp.OAToggleButton
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OAJspComponent, OAJspRequirementsInterface, Serializable

    public class OAToggleButton
extends OAButton
    Button that has two states: Selected and Not Selected. Can be used in a OAButtonGroup so that only one button in the group is selected at a time. 
        [Java Code]
    OAToggleButton tog = new OAToggleButton("testUp.gif","testDown.gif");
    tog.setSelected(true);
    buttonGroup.add(tog);
    form.add("togTest", tog);
    ....
    [HTML Code]
    <input type="image" name="<%=form.getToggleButton("togUser").getName()%>" <%=form.getToggleButton("togUser").getSource()%> SRC="testUp.gif" ALT="User Info" border="0">
    output =>
    <input type="image" name="oacommand_7_togUser" SRC="testUp.gif" src="testUp.gif">
    See Also:
    OAButtonGroup, Serialized Form
